          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Turkey talks </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: The two-hour direct talks led to a prisoner exchange, but Russia continued its offensive.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          On May 16, delegations from Russia and Ukraine met in Istanbul for the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-spotlight-h2-2-first-direct-talks" target="_blank">first direct talks</a> in over three years. Before the negotiations, Ukraine had pushed for a 30-day ceasefire, which Russia rejected. Meanwhile, Russia demanded Ukraine cede control over four major regions: Zaporizhzhia, Kherson, Donetsk, and Luhansk, as a precondition for a ceasefire, which Ukraine deemed unacceptable.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         However, both sides agreed to exchange 1,000 prisoners of war, marking the largest swap since the conflict began. President Trump <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-spotlight-h2-3-announced-plans" target="_blank">announced plans</a> to talk with the presidents of opposing nations to end the bloodshed. Critics say Trump‚Äôs stance shields Russia from accountability in the conflict. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Analysts say that Russia has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-spotlight-h2-4-consistently-undermined" target="_blank">consistently undermined</a> peace efforts while Trump's administration has pushed for concessions, including cessions and NATO restrictions for Ukraine, with little response from Moscow. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        After the failed peace talks in Turkey, Ukraine reported that Russia launched a record <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-spotlight-h2-5-273-drones-overnight" target="_blank">273 drones overnight</a>. These targeted multiple regions, including Kyiv, and the Ukrainian air force stated it destroyed 88 drones, while 128 veered from their original course without causing damage. Deputy PM Yulia Svyrydenko called the attack ‚Äúa clear goal to continue killing civilians.‚Äù</p>
        </mj-text>
