          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
        Afghanistan faces abandonment
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: The US administration is significantly undermining support for Afghans by slashing key programs.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The Trump administration has reduced US support for humanitarian and development aid globally, with <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-analysis-h1-6-afghanistan-hit-the-hardest" target="_blank">Afghanistan hit the hardest</a>. They were the largest humanitarian donor to Afghanistan, contributing over $3.8B since 2021. The decision to cut all funding for programs, including the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-analysis-h1-7-world-food-program" target="_blank">World Food Program</a> in Afghanistan, will affect 400,000 malnourished women and children.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The administration also failed to extend <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-analysis-h1-8-temporary-protected-status" target="_blank">Temporary Protected Status</a> for over 9000 Afghans and paused <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-analysis-h1-9-special-immigrant-visas" target="_blank">Special Immigrant Visas</a>, breaking the promises made to Afghans. These choices abandon vulnerable people behind and damage America‚Äôs moral and strategic credibility. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          While the US still engages with the Taliban on issues, including hostage talks, there is no clear policy or accountability for human rights. The administration seems determined to sever all ties with Afghanistan. These policies show a retreat from responsibility by the US and abandon Afghans to suffer the consequences of war. 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
