      <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/geopolitical-map-us-libya-palestine-pakistan-russia-india-china.png" alt="Illustration showing international geopolitical connections between the United States, Libya, Palestine, Pakistan, Russia, India, and China" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá®üá≥ China - Anti-dumping duties.</strong> China imposed anti-dumping duties as high as 74.9% on US imports of POM copolymers, a type of industrial plastic. This decision follows a probe initiated in May 2024 after the US raised tariffs on Chinese goods. Meanwhile, imports from the EU will be taxed at 34.5%. This measure follows a 90-day tariff truce between the US and China (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-worldwide-10-more-tariff-issues" target="_blank">more tariff issues</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá≥ India - Professor arrested.</strong> Indian professor Ali Khan Mahmudabad was detained over a social media post criticizing India‚Äôs military briefings on its operation against Pakistan. He found it hypocritical to applaud women officers while ignoring violence against Muslims. He was charged with promoting communal disharmony, and his comments sparked backlash and support (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-worldwide-11-the-dissenting-academic" target="_blank">the dissenting academic</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáµüá∏ Palestine - Trump makes plans.</strong> The Trump administration is reportedly considering relocating up to 1 Mn Palestinians from Gaza to Libya. Talks with Libyan leaders will involve potentially unfreezing Libyan assets as part of the agreement. The plan faces significant criticism and logistical hurdles, with many calling it both unrealistic and unjust (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-worldwide-12-a-sweeping-retreat" target="_blank">a sweeping retreat</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá∑üá∫ Russia - Putin taps into MENA.</strong> Putin has invited Arab League leaders to the first-ever Russia-Arab Summit, set for October 15. As announced during the 34th Arab League Summit, Putin aims to strengthen dialogue and cooperation. He expressed confidence that the summit would boost mutual ties and support peace and stability across the Middle East and North Africa (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-worldwide-13-putin-s-plans" target="_blank">Putin‚Äôs plans</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáµüá∏ Palestine - Hamas leader's body found.</strong> 
            As per reports, Muhammad Sinwar‚Äôs body was recovered from a Khan Younis tunnel along with the remains of 10 of his aides, confirming his death. However, an official confirmation is yet to be made. He was the younger brother of the former Hamas leader in Gaza, Yahya Sinwar, who was killed by the IDF in southern Gaza last October. According to a separate report, Zakaria Sinwar, another brother, was killed in an Israeli airstrike on Saturday night (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-may-25-worldwide-14-sinwar-annihilated" target="_blank">Sinwar annihilated</a>). 
          </p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá≥ India - More water drama.</strong> 
